title: For Sale:  Swedish Mauser Bayonet
postcontent: I am selling an M/1896 pattern Swedish Mauser Bayonet. It is my understanding that in addition to the M/1896 rifle, this pattern bayonet was issued with the M/38 short rifle as well as the AG42b Ljungmann self-loader. It should have full compatability with any of these rifles.The numbers on the bayonet and sheath do not match, however interestingly enough they are only 3 apart (462 and 465 respectively). This strikes me as an unlikely coincedence, however ultimately that is for the buyer to judge. Both the bayonet and sheath are in excellent condition, as the pictures should show.The markings on the sheath, to the best of my understanding, indicate that this bayonet was manufactured by Eskiltuna Jernmanufaktur, and assigned to rifle 1191, 9th Company, 18th Infantry Division. The "D" stamped over the Company marker probably indicates that the bayonet was removed from the 9th company, however remained assigned to the 18th Infantry division.The markings on the blade reveal the same manufacturer as the sheath, Eskiltuna Jernmanufaktur. Not pictured is the marking "A3", the meaning of which I do not know. Often, the Swedish "A" stands for "Artilleriet" (artillery), however whether that is what this particular "A" stands for is purely speculation.The leather bayonet frog is highly functional and an aesthetic match to the bayonet and sheath, however is not original to this model of bayonet.This set is a cool collector set on its own, or a fully functional complement to your Swedish Military surplus rifle. Again, the blade and bayonet are truly in excellent condition, and I am happy to provide higher res images on request. I will be happy to ship this item anywhere in the United States.
